## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-103">Par défaut, le mot clé d’aide pour une classe est fourni par le <xref:System.Type.FullName%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> valeur de propriété.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-103">By default, the Help keyword for a class is given by the <xref:System.Type.FullName%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property value.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-104">Pour les membres, le mot clé d’aide est fourni par le nom complet du type qui a déclaré la propriété, ainsi que le nom de la propriété.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-104">For members, the Help keyword is given by the full name of the type that declared the property, plus the property name itself.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-105">Par exemple, considérez le <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> propriété sur le <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button?displayProperty=nameWithType> contrôle.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-105">For example, consider the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property on the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button?displayProperty=nameWithType> control.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-106">Le mot clé class est « System.Windows.Forms.Button », mais le <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> mot clé de propriété est « System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text », car le <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> propriété est déclarée sur le <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control?displayProperty=nameWithType> (classe), plutôt que la <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button?displayProperty=nameWithType> classe lui-même ; le <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button?displayProperty=nameWithType> classe hérite de la propriété.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-106">The class keyword is "System.Windows.Forms.Button", but the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property keyword is "System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text", because the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control.Text%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property is declared on the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Control?displayProperty=nameWithType> class, rather than the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button?displayProperty=nameWithType> class itself; the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button?displayProperty=nameWithType> class inherits the property.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-107">En revanche, le <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button.DialogResult%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> propriété est déclarée sur le <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button?displayProperty=nameWithType> de classe, de sorte que son mot clé est « System.Windows.Forms.Button.DialogResult ».</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-107">By contrast, the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button.DialogResult%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property is declared on the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Button?displayProperty=nameWithType> class, so its keyword is "System.Windows.Forms.Button.DialogResult".</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-108">Lorsque le système d’aide Obtient les mots clés, il regarde d’abord <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.HelpKeywordAttribute>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-108">When the Help system gets the keywords, it will first look at <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.HelpKeywordAttribute>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-109">Au niveau de la classe, il retourne la chaîne spécifiée par le <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.HelpKeywordAttribute>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-109">At the class level, it will return the string specified by the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.HelpKeywordAttribute>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-110">Cela ne sera pas utilisé pour les membres du type en question, qui reflète toujours nom complet du type déclarant, ainsi que le nom du membre.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-110">This will not be used for members of the type in question, which will still reflect the declaring type's actual full name, plus the member name.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-111">Cet attribut prend en charge des classes fortement typées qui sont associés à documentation courants, mais des ID d’aide distincts.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-111">This attribute supports strongly typed classes that have associated common documentation but distinct Help IDs.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-112">L’exemple de code suivant montre comment substituer ce comportement de système d’aide en plaçant l’attribut sur le membre lui-même.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-112">The following code example shows how to override this Help system behavior by placing the attribute on the member itself.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-113">Voici les mots clés pour la classe suivante, appelée `DemoComponent`:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-113">These are the keywords for the following class, called `DemoComponent`:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-114">Mot clé de classe : «`System.ComponentModel.Component`» (`DemoNamespace.DemoComponent`)</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-114">Class keyword: "`System.ComponentModel.Component`" (`DemoNamespace.DemoComponent`)</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-115">Mot clé de Property1 : «`DemoNamespace.DemoComponent.Property1`» (valeur par défaut)</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-115">Property1 keyword: "`DemoNamespace.DemoComponent.Property1`" (default)</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-116">Mot clé de Property2 : «`SomeNamespace.SomeOtherClass.Property2`» (`DemoNamespace.DemoComponent.Property2`)</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-116">Property2 keyword: "`SomeNamespace.SomeOtherClass.Property2`" (`DemoNamespace.DemoComponent.Property2`)</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
[HelpKeywordAttribute(typeof(Component))]  
public class DemoComponent : Component  
{  
    public string Property1  
    {  
        get  
        {  
            return "";  
        }  
    }  
  
    [HelpKeywordAttribute("SomeNamespace.SomeOtherClass.Property2")]  
    public string Property2  
    {  
        get  
        {  
            return "";  
        }  
    }  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-117">L’exemple de code suivant montre comment utiliser le <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.HelpKeywordAttribute> classe pour spécifier un mot clé de contexte.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-117">The following code example demonstrates using the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.HelpKeywordAttribute> class to specify a context keyword.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5fde1-118">Pour obtenir une explication complète de cet exemple de code, consultez [Comment : appliquer des attributs dans les contrôles Windows Forms](~/docs/framework/winforms/controls/how-to-apply-attributes-in-windows-forms-controls.md).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5fde1-118">For a complete explanation of this code example, see [How to: Apply Attributes in Windows Forms Controls](~/docs/framework/winforms/controls/how-to-apply-attributes-in-windows-forms-controls.md).</span></span>  
  
